&gt;&gt; Catherine Kerst: [inaudible].

00:05:11.840 --> 00:05:13.140
&gt;&gt; Anuradha Nehru: And, of course,

00:05:13.140 --> 00:05:16.300
the other characteristic feature is
a lot of the poetry and the lyrics

00:05:16.300 --> 00:05:18.780
that we use for Kuchipudi
dance comes

00:05:18.780 --> 00:05:26.400
from the poets written
in the language Telugu.

00:05:26.400 --> 00:05:30.750
So, a lot of the dances
are choreographed

00:05:30.750 --> 00:05:33.880
to poetry written by
Telugu or Sanskrit.

00:05:33.880 --> 00:05:36.870
Whereas, the other forms
use other languages

00:05:36.870 --> 00:05:40.400
that are more common
in their regions.

