when I asked them the questions

00:09:37.350 --> 00:09:39.230
to why they dance, and one

00:09:39.230 --> 00:09:42.540
of them was their connection
to their heritage.

00:09:42.540 --> 00:09:45.920
And, the second was the sense
of freedom and liberation

00:09:45.920 --> 00:09:48.260
from their mundane, routine lives.

00:09:48.260 --> 00:09:53.140
The third was storytelling which
they felt, for that period of time,

00:09:53.140 --> 00:09:57.220
for them time is suspended and
they take their audience with them

00:09:57.220 --> 00:09:59.770
into the stories they
tell through dance.

00:09:59.770 --> 00:10:03.370
And, the fourth was the sense
of community that they feel

00:10:03.370 --> 00:10:07.800
and the most open and honest
relationships that they have is

00:10:07.800 --> 00:10:10.720
with their fellow dancers
and how special that is.

00:10:10.720 --> 00:10:15.020
So, I just felt those thoughts
were so well articulated

00:10:15.020 --> 00:10:19.030
by the Kalanidhi dancers that
we decided to develop work

00:10:19.030 --> 00:10:20.700
around those four concepts.

